title: ConfigMgr Remote Control Users
description: Members in this group can view and control this computer using Configuration Manager Remote Control

title: Offer Remote Assistance Helpers
description: Members in this group can offer Remote Assistance to the users of this machine

title: Organization Management
description: Members of this management role group have permissions to manage Exchange objects and their properties in the Exchange organization. Members can also delegate role groups and management roles in the organization. This role group shouldn't be deleted.

dn: CN=Public Folder Management,OU=Microsoft Exchange Security Groups,DC=e-mordovia,DC=ru
title: Public Folder Management
description: Members of this management role group can manage public folders. Members can create and delete public folders and manage public folder settings such as replicas, quotas, age limits, and permissions as well as mail-enable and mail-disable public folders.

title: Recipient Management
description: Members of this management role group have rights to create, manage, and remove Exchange recipient objects in the Exchange organization.

dn: CN=View-Only Organization Management,OU=Microsoft Exchange Security Groups,DC=e-mordovia,DC=ru
title: View-Only Organization Management
description: Members of this management role group can view recipient and configuration objects and their properties in the Exchange organization.

title: UM Management
description: Members of this management role group can manage Unified Messaging organization, server, and recipient configuration.

title: Help Desk
description: Members of this management role group can view and manage the configuration for individual recipients and view recipients in an Exchange organization. Members of this role group can only manage the configuration each user can manage on his or her own mailbox. Additional  permissions can be added by assigning additional management roles to this role group.

title: Records Management
description: Members of this management role group can configure compliance features such as retention policy tags, message classifications, transport rules, and more.

title: Discovery Management
description: Members of this management role group can perform searches of mailboxes in the Exchange organization for data that meets specific criteria.

title: Server Management
description: Members of this management role group have permissions to manage all Exchange servers within the Exchange organization, but members don't have permissions to perform operations that have global impact in the Exchange organization.

title: Delegated Setup
description: Members of this management role group have permissions to install and uninstall Exchange on provisioned servers. Removal of this role group will prevent you from performing future delegated setup operations.This role group shouldn't be deleted.

title: Hygiene Management
description: Members of this management role group can manage Exchange anti-spam features and grant permissions for antivirus products to integrate with Exchange.

title: Exchange Servers
description: This group contains all the Exchange servers. This group shouldn't be deleted.
memberOf: CN=Managed Availability Servers,OU=Microsoft Exchange Security Groups,DC=e-mordovia,DC=ru

dn: CN=Exchange Trusted Subsystem,OU=Microsoft Exchange Security Groups,DC=e-mordovia,DC=ru
title: Exchange Trusted Subsystem
description: This group contains Exchange servers that run Exchange cmdlets on behalf of users via the management service. Its members have permission to read and modify all Exchange configuration, as well as user accounts and groups. This group should not be deleted.
memberOf: CN=Exchange Windows Permissions,OU=Microsoft Exchange Security Groups,DC=e-mordovia,DC=ru

dn: CN=Exchange All Hosted Organizations,OU=Microsoft Exchange Security Groups,DC=e-mordovia,DC=ru
title: Exchange All Hosted Organizations
description: This group contains all the Exchange Hosted Organization Mailboxes groups. It's used for applying password setting objects to all hosted mailboxes.This group shouldn't be deleted.

dn: CN=Exchange Windows Permissions,OU=Microsoft Exchange Security Groups,DC=e-mordovia,DC=ru
title: Exchange Windows Permissions
description: This group contains Exchange servers that run Exchange cmdlets on behalf of users via the management service. Its members have permission to read and modify all Windows accounts and groups. This group should not be deleted.

title: ExchangeLegacyInterop
description: This group is for interoperability with Exchange 2003 servers within the same forest. This group should not be deleted.

dn: CN=Exchange Install Domain Servers,CN=Microsoft Exchange System Objects,DC=e-mordovia,DC=ru
title: Exchange Install Domain Servers
description: This group is used during Exchange setup and is not intended to be used for other purposes.

title: Compliance Management
description: This role group will allow a specified user, responsible for compliance, to properly configure and manage compliance settings within Exchange in accordance with their policy.

dn: CN=Managed Availability Servers,OU=Microsoft Exchange Security Groups,DC=e-mordovia,DC=ru
title: Managed Availability Servers
description: This group contains all the Managed Availability servers. This group shouldn't be deleted.

description: Built-in group used by Internet Information Services.

title: Denied RODC Password Replication Group

title: Read-only Domain Controllers
description: Members of this group are Read-Only Domain Controllers in the domain

title: Event Log Readers
description: Members of this group can read event logs from local machine

title: Enterprise Read-only Domain Controllers
description: Members of this group are Read-Only Domain Controllers in the enterprise

title: Certificate Service DCOM Access
description: Members of this group are allowed to connect to Certification Authorities in the enterprise

title: RDS Remote Access Servers
description: Servers in this group enable users of RemoteApp programs and personal virtual desktops access to these resources. In Internet-facing deployments, these servers are typically deployed in an edge network. This group needs to be populated on servers running RD Connection Broker. RD Gateway servers and RD Web Access servers used in the deployment need to be in this group.

title: RDS Endpoint Servers
description: Servers in this group run virtual machines and host sessions where users RemoteApp programs and personal virtual desktops run. This group needs to be populated on servers running RD Connection Broker. RD Session Host servers and RD Virtualization Host servers used in the deployment need to be in this group.

title: RDS Management Servers
description: Servers in this group can perform routine administrative actions on servers running Remote Desktop Services. This group needs to be populated on all servers in a Remote Desktop Services deployment. The servers running the RDS Central Management service must be included in this group.

title: Hyper-V Administrators
description: Members of this group have complete and unrestricted access to all features of Hyper-V.

title: Cloneable Domain Controllers
description: Members of this group that are domain controllers may be cloned.

title: Access Control Assistance Operators
description: Members of this group can remotely query authorization attributes and permissions for resources on this computer.

title: Remote Management Users
description: Members of this group can access WMI resources over management protocols (such as WS-Management via the Windows Remote Management service). This applies only to WMI namespaces that grant access to the user.

title: Protected Users
description: Members of this group are afforded additional protections against authentication security threats. See http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=298939 for more information.

title: Kse Administrators
description: Members of this group are granted top-level rights to use Kaspersky Security for Microsoft Exchange Servers. Members of this group monitor the operation of Kaspersky Security components, application database updates, and the status of protection on Microsoft Exchange servers. Members of this group can grant other users restricted rights to use Kaspersky Security.

title: Kse Security Officers
description: Members of this group are granted rights to manage data leakage protection through Kaspersky Security.

title: Kse AV Security Officers
description: Members of this group are granted rights to view the protection status on Microsoft Exchange servers and generate application reports. Besides, members of this group have restricted rights to manage Backup objects, as well as rights to view all the application settings except for those in the Data Leak Prevention section.

title: Kse AV Operators
description: Members of this group are granted minimum rights to use Kaspersky Security. Members of this group can view the status of protection on Microsoft Exchange servers and generate Anti-Virus and Anti-Spam reports.

title: Kse Watchdog Service
description: This group contains accounts that are used for running the services of Kaspersky Security for Microsoft Exchange Servers.
